      "date": "2013-04-29 16:53:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nDefinitely an improvement I think. \n\nI see that you added upgrade support for this, so it won't break LLNL, great.  I don't see where it removes the old seq-NNNNNNNN-lastid file?  This may be incorrect if any new objects were allocated in that sequence, so it would be unsafe to use in case of a rollback. I guess still better than reverting to no LASTID at all, but dangerous...",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
